	<h2><a href="/book/EgoEnemy">Ego Is the Enemy - by Ryan Holiday</a></h2>
	<small>Date read: 2016-08-01. How strongly I recommend it: <strong>9</strong>/10</small>
	<p>Forget yourself and focus on the work. Be humble and persistent. Value discipline and results, not passion and confidence. Be lesser, do more. This message is crucial, but the opposite of almost every other book. I wish everyone would read this. I need to re-read it each year. It's that important. It's easy to read this and say “oh yeah I've got my ego under control”, but the problem is deeper than that.</p>
