	<div class="abook" data-rating="9" data-title="Fluent Forever - by Gabriel Wyner" data-date="2014-08-18">
	<figure><a href="/book/FluentForever"><img src="/images/FluentForever.gif" alt="Fluent Forever - by Gabriel Wyner"></a></figure>
	<h2><a href="/book/FluentForever">Fluent Forever - by Gabriel Wyner</a></h2>
	<small>Date read: 2014-08-18. How strongly I recommend it: <strong>9</strong>/10</small>
	<p>Forget Rosetta Stone, Pimsleur, and the rest. I really believe this is the best way to learn another language, by far. Using the most up-to-date techniques and insights, and a unique emphasis on getting the sounds correct first. It's not easy, but it's much more effective than any other program or guide. Highly recommended if you're serious, and ready to do it.</p>
	<p><strong><a href="/book/FluentForever">Read my notes</a></strong>, or go to the <a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/0385348118?tag=sivers-20">Amazon page</a> for details and reviews.</p>
